 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|2|9|df=y}}
 |Aux4 = 1.432
 |ShortSummary = Mackenzie decides to assign the group a task and then they are free to go home. However, he forces Quinn to stay with him in his [[Travel trailer|caravan]]. Mackenzie admits that although he is rich enough, he cannot let the three million euros go because of his reputation. The rest are instructed to pick up supplies to produce [[MDMA|ecstasy]] from a cabana and send them to the abandoned village. En route Baxter returns for Carmen. After making the ecstasy, Carmen exits the van to wait for Baxter later. They deliver the ecstasy in a nightclub. After they receive five million euros as payment, they drive back to Mackenzie's caravan in time to save Quinn. It is revealed that Mackenzie made them produce fake tablets to fool the nightclub owners. Mackenzie lets them go, instructing them to board a cargo container, which will take them back to the mainland via ferry. As an extra, he allows them to keep the money. Baxter is forced to leave Carmen behind, though he intends to contact her when they arrive in Barcelona. However, later they find that Mackenzie tricked them; the ferry arrives in [[Morocco]] and the money is confiscated by armed men.
